Subject: [PATCH 17/17] Migrate observability.ts to /interview TELOS schema

Upstream issue: danielmiessler/Personal_AI_Infrastructure#1153

The /interview skill and Pulse/Observability/observability.ts use
two different TELOS schemas. /interview Phase 2 + Phase 4 populate
a directory-based layout (IDEAL_STATE/, CURRENT_STATE/); the Pulse
Observability dashboard reads a flat-file layout (CURRENT.md,
2036.md) and has zero references to the directories Interview
produces. After running a complete /interview, the Life Dashboard
renders empty/null for several major sections — looks broken even
when the user did everything right.

Per Q3 (user's choice in this pai-nix patch series): migrate
observability to interview's schema. Interview's directory layout
is the newer/richer schema and should win.

Fix scope (5 hunks):

  1. TELOS_FILE_ALLOWLIST extension — permit
     IDEAL_STATE/{HEALTH,MONEY,FREEDOM,RELATIONSHIPS,CREATIVE}.md
     and CURRENT_STATE/SNAPSHOT.md so the file editor endpoint
     can write to those files.

  2. validateTelosFileName — drop the blanket "/" rejection.
     The allowlist itself is the authority on which slash-bearing
     paths are valid; "\\" and ".." remain rejected as defense in
     depth.

  3. parseGoals — add header-form support (same fix family as
     patch 0013 for GenerateTelosSummary). Bullet form continues
     to win; "## G0: text" / "### G0: text" are the new fallback
     that catches what /interview writes.

  4. handleLifeHome — read CURRENT_STATE/SNAPSHOT.md. Fall back to
     legacy CURRENT.md if SNAPSHOT.md absent (preserves behavior
     for users with hand-maintained flat CURRENT.md). 2036.md
     reader kept (best-effort) — file may not exist, timelineBlocks
     resolves to 0.

  5. handleTelosOverview — surface idealState (5 dimensions read
     via parseSections from IDEAL_STATE/*.md) and snapshot (parsed
     from CURRENT_STATE/SNAPSHOT.md). Both fields previously hard-
     coded to null.

Files touched (paths relative to upstream source root):

  Releases/v5.0.0/.claude/PAI/PULSE/Observability/observability.ts   :1086, 1098, 1554, 1672-1675, 2369

Total: 1 file, 5 hunks.

Co-existence: patch 0006 modified observability.ts at lines 69, 152,
1650 (Pulse case-sensitivity fix). Non-overlapping with this
patch's targets at 1086, 1098, 1554, 1672, 2369.

Hunks generated via `diff -u` against the post-0016 result/ tree.
No hand-counted @@ headers.

Out of scope (per ISA Out of Scope):

  - Dedicated /api/life/ideal-state endpoint — the
    handleTelosOverview field is sufficient for current
    consumers; if a separate endpoint is needed later, follow-up
    patch.
  - Backfilling /interview to also write CURRENT.md / 2036.md
    legacy files — wrong direction; the issue's explicit guidance
    is to migrate observability TO interview's schema.
  - Running parseSections() on CURRENT.md fallback when SNAPSHOT
    is present — handleLifeHome's existing code expects a flat
    CURRENT.md format; SNAPSHOT.md is structurally similar enough
    that parseBoldFields and parseNumberedList work on either.
